race.comment: ARATIRI (12) is yet to miss a drum in four starts over this course and distance and will be cherry-ripe for this. Nicely placed to find winning ways. SACRED BULL (9) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and must be respected out of the Bruce camp. Top-three credentials. LUCONI (7) has won two of his past three and winning rider Lerena sticks. In the mix. The well-related TOBA (15) (half to G3 winner Keshi Boom) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on. SAN JOSE BOY (8) looks close to an elusive win following a sound third over 1400m at Sunshine Coast, beaten 1.3 lengths. In form and expected to run well.
